verses.text: And this \add is\add* the \w blessing|strong="H1293"\w*, wherewith \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* the \w man|strong="H0376"\w* of \w God|strong="H0430"\w* \w blessed|strong="H1288"\w* the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* his \w death|strong="H4194"\w*.

And he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w came|strong="H0935"\w* from \w Sinai|strong="H5514"\w*, and rose \w up|strong="H2224"\w* from \w Seir|strong="H8165"\w* unto them; he shined \w forth|strong="H3313"\w* from \w mount|strong="H2022"\w* \w Paran|strong="H6290"\w*, and he \w came|strong="H0857"\w* with ten \w thousands|strong="H7233"\w* of \w saints|strong="H6944"\w*: from his right \w hand|strong="H3225"\w* \add went\add* a \w fiery|strong="H0799"\w* \w law|strong="H1881"\w* for them.\f + \fr 33.2 \ft a fiery…: Heb. a fire of law\f*

\w Yea|strong="H0637"\w*, he \w loved|strong="H2245"\w* the \w people|strong="H5971"\w*; all his \w saints|strong="H6918"\w* \add are\add* in thy \w hand|strong="H3027"\w*: and they sat \w down|strong="H8497"\w* at thy \w feet|strong="H7272"\w*; \add every one\add* shall \w receive|strong="H5375"\w* of thy \w words|strong="H1703"\w*.

\w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* \w commanded|strong="H6680"\w* us a \w law|strong="H8451"\w*, \add even\add* the \w inheritance|strong="H4181"\w* of the \w congregation|strong="H6952"\w* of \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w*.

And he was \w king|strong="H4428"\w* in \w Jeshurun|strong="H3484"\w*, when the \w heads|strong="H7218"\w* of the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \add and\add* the \w tribes|strong="H7626"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* were \w gathered|strong="H0622"\w* \w together|strong="H3162"\w*.
¶ Let \w Reuben|strong="H7205"\w* \w live|strong="H2421"\w*, and not \w die|strong="H4191"\w*; and let \add not\add* his \w men|strong="H4962"\w* be \w few|strong="H4557"\w*.

¶ And this \add is the blessing\add* of \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*: and he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, \w Hear|strong="H8085"\w*, \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, the \w voice|strong="H6963"\w* of \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*, and \w bring|strong="H0935"\w* him unto his \w people|strong="H5971"\w*: let his \w hands|strong="H3027"\w* be \w sufficient|strong="H7227"\w* for him; and be thou an \w help|strong="H5828"\w* \add to him\add* from his \w enemies|strong="H6862"\w*.

¶ And of \w Levi|strong="H3878"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, \add Let\add* thy \w Thummim|strong="H8550"\w* and thy \w Urim|strong="H0224"\w* \add be\add* with thy \w holy|strong="H2623"\w* \w one|strong="H0376"\w*, whom thou didst \w prove|strong="H5254"\w* at \w Massah|strong="H4532"\w*, \add and with\add* whom thou didst \w strive|strong="H7378"\w* at the \w waters|strong="H4325"\w* of \w Meribah|strong="H4809"\w*;

Who \w said|strong="H0559"\w* unto his \w father|strong="H0001"\w* and to his \w mother|strong="H0517"\w*, I have not \w seen|strong="H7200"\w* him; neither did he \w acknowledge|strong="H5234"\w* his \w brethren|strong="H0251"\w*, nor \w knew|strong="H3045"\w* his own \w children|strong="H1121"\w*: for they have \w observed|strong="H8104"\w* thy \w word|strong="H0565"\w*, and \w kept|strong="H5341"\w* thy \w covenant|strong="H1285"\w*.

They shall \w teach|strong="H3384"\w* \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* thy \w judgments|strong="H4941"\w*, and \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* thy \w law|strong="H8451"\w*: they shall \w put|strong="H7760"\w* \w incense|strong="H6988"\w* \w before|strong="H0639"\w* thee, and whole burnt \w sacrifice|strong="H3632"\w* upon thine \w altar|strong="H4196"\w*.\f + \fr 33.10 \ft They shall teach: or, Let them teach\f*\f + \fr 33.10 \ft they shall put: or, let them put\f*\f + \fr 33.10 \ft before…: Heb. at thy nose\f*

\w Bless|strong="H1288"\w*, \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, his \w substance|strong="H2428"\w*, and \w accept|strong="H7521"\w* the \w work|strong="H6467"\w* of his \w hands|strong="H3027"\w*: \w smite|strong="H4272"\w* through the \w loins|strong="H4975"\w* of them that \w rise|strong="H6965"\w* against him, and of them that \w hate|strong="H8130"\w* him, that they \w rise|strong="H6965"\w* \w not|strong="H4480"\w* \w again|strong="H6965"\w*.

¶ \add And\add* of \w Benjamin|strong="H1144"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, The \w beloved|strong="H3039"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* shall \w dwell|strong="H7931"\w* in \w safety|strong="H0983"\w* by him; \add and the \+nd Lord\+nd*\add* shall \w cover|strong="H2653"\w* him all the \w day|strong="H3117"\w* long, and he shall \w dwell|strong="H7931"\w* between his \w shoulders|strong="H3802"\w*.

¶ And of \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, \w Blessed|strong="H1288"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add be\add* his \w land|strong="H0776"\w*, for the precious \w things|strong="H4022"\w* of \w heaven|strong="H8064"\w*, for the \w dew|strong="H2919"\w*, and for the \w deep|strong="H8415"\w* that coucheth \w beneath|strong="H7257"\w*,

And for the \w precious|strong="H4022"\w* \w fruits|strong="H8393"\w* \add brought forth\add* by the \w sun|strong="H8121"\w*, and for the precious \w things|strong="H4022"\w* put \w forth|strong="H1645"\w* by the \w moon|strong="H3391"\w*,\f + \fr 33.14 \ft put: Heb. thrust\f*\f + \fr 33.14 \ft moon: Heb. moons\f*

And for the chief \w things|strong="H7218"\w* of the \w ancient|strong="H6924"\w* \w mountains|strong="H2042"\w*, and for the precious \w things|strong="H4022"\w* of the \w lasting|strong="H5769"\w* \w hills|strong="H1389"\w*,

And for the precious \w things|strong="H4022"\w* of the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w* and \w fulness|strong="H4393"\w* thereof, and \add for\add* the good \w will|strong="H7522"\w* of him that \w dwelt|strong="H7931"\w* in the \w bush|strong="H5572"\w*: let \add the blessing\add* \w come|strong="H0935"\w* upon the \w head|strong="H7218"\w* of \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w*, and upon the top of the \w head|strong="H6936"\w* of him \add that was\add* \w separated|strong="H5139"\w* from his \w brethren|strong="H0251"\w*.

His \w glory|strong="H1926"\w* \add is like\add* the \w firstling|strong="H1060"\w* of his \w bullock|strong="H7794"\w*, and his \w horns|strong="H7161"\w* \add are like\add* the \w horns|strong="H7161"\w* of \w unicorns|strong="H7214"\w*: with them he shall \w push|strong="H5055"\w* the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w together|strong="H3162"\w* to the \w ends|strong="H0657"\w* of the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w*: and they \add are\add* the ten \w thousands|strong="H7233"\w* of \w Ephraim|strong="H0669"\w*, and they \add are\add* the \w thousands|strong="H0505"\w* of \w Manasseh|strong="H4519"\w*.\f + \fr 33.17 \ft unicorns: Heb. an unicorn\f*

¶ And of \w Zebulun|strong="H2074"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, \w Rejoice|strong="H8055"\w*, \w Zebulun|strong="H2074"\w*, in thy going \w out|strong="H3318"\w*; and, \w Issachar|strong="H3485"\w*, in thy \w tents|strong="H0168"\w*.

They shall \w call|strong="H7121"\w* the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* unto the \w mountain|strong="H2022"\w*; there they shall \w offer|strong="H2076"\w* \w sacrifices|strong="H2077"\w* of \w righteousness|strong="H6664"\w*: for they shall \w suck|strong="H3243"\w* \add of\add* the \w abundance|strong="H8228"\w* of the \w seas|strong="H3220"\w*, and \add of\add* \w treasures|strong="H8226"\w* \w hid|strong="H2934"\w* in the \w sand|strong="H2344"\w*.

¶ And of \w Gad|strong="H1410"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, \w Blessed|strong="H1288"\w* \add be\add* he that \w enlargeth|strong="H7337"\w* \w Gad|strong="H1410"\w*: he \w dwelleth|strong="H7931"\w* as a \w lion|strong="H3833"\w*, and \w teareth|strong="H2963"\w* the \w arm|strong="H2220"\w* \w with|strong="H0637"\w* the crown of the \w head|strong="H6936"\w*.

And he \w provided|strong="H7200"\w* the first \w part|strong="H7225"\w* for himself, because there, \add in\add* a \w portion|strong="H2513"\w* of the \w lawgiver|strong="H2710"\w*, \add was he\add* \w seated|strong="H5603"\w*; and he \w came|strong="H0857"\w* with the \w heads|strong="H7218"\w* of the \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, he \w executed|strong="H6213"\w* the \w justice|strong="H6666"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and his \w judgments|strong="H4941"\w* with \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*.\f + \fr 33.21 \ft seated: Heb. cieled\f*

¶ And of \w Dan|strong="H1835"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, \w Dan|strong="H1835"\w* \add is\add* a \w lion’s|strong="H0738"\w* \w whelp|strong="H1482"\w*: he shall \w leap|strong="H2187"\w* from \w Bashan|strong="H1316"\w*.

¶ And of \w Naphtali|strong="H5321"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, O \w Naphtali|strong="H5321"\w*, \w satisfied|strong="H7649"\w* with \w favour|strong="H7522"\w*, and \w full|strong="H4392"\w* with the \w blessing|strong="H1293"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: \w possess|strong="H3423"\w* thou the \w west|strong="H3220"\w* and the \w south|strong="H1864"\w*.

¶ And of \w Asher|strong="H0836"\w* he \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, \add Let\add* \w Asher|strong="H0836"\w* \add be\add* \w blessed|strong="H1288"\w* with \w children|strong="H1121"\w*; let him be \w acceptable|strong="H7521"\w* to his \w brethren|strong="H0251"\w*, and let him \w dip|strong="H2881"\w* his \w foot|strong="H7272"\w* in \w oil|strong="H8081"\w*.

Thy \w shoes|strong="H4515"\w* \add shall be\add* \w iron|strong="H1270"\w* and \w brass|strong="H5178"\w*; and as thy \w days|strong="H3117"\w*, \add so shall\add* thy \w strength|strong="H1679"\w* \add be\add*.\f + \fr 33.25 \ft Thy shoes: or, Under thy shoes\f*

¶ \add There is\add* none like unto the \w God|strong="H0410"\w* of \w Jeshurun|strong="H3484"\w*, \add who\add* \w rideth|strong="H7392"\w* upon the \w heaven|strong="H8064"\w* in thy \w help|strong="H5828"\w*, and in his \w excellency|strong="H1346"\w* on the \w sky|strong="H7834"\w*.

The \w eternal|strong="H6924"\w* \w God|strong="H0430"\w* \add is thy\add* \w refuge|strong="H4585"\w*, and underneath \add are\add* the \w everlasting|strong="H5769"\w* \w arms|strong="H2220"\w*: and he shall thrust \w out|strong="H1644"\w* the \w enemy|strong="H0341"\w* from \w before|strong="H6440"\w* thee; and shall \w say|strong="H0559"\w*, \w Destroy|strong="H8045"\w* \add them\add*.

\w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* then shall \w dwell|strong="H7931"\w* in \w safety|strong="H0983"\w* \w alone|strong="H0910"\w*: the \w fountain|strong="H5869"\w* of \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \add shall be\add* upon a \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w corn|strong="H1715"\w* and \w wine|strong="H8492"\w*; also his \w heavens|strong="H8064"\w* shall drop \w down|strong="H6201"\w* \w dew|strong="H2919"\w*.

\w Happy|strong="H0835"\w* \add art\add* thou, O \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*: who \add is\add* like unto thee, O \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w saved|strong="H3467"\w* by the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, the \w shield|strong="H4043"\w* of thy \w help|strong="H5828"\w*, and who \add is\add* the \w sword|strong="H2719"\w* of thy \w excellency|strong="H1346"\w*! and thine \w enemies|strong="H0341"\w* shall be found \w liars|strong="H3584"\w* unto thee; and thou shalt \w tread|strong="H1869"\w* upon their high \w places|strong="H1116"\w*.\f + \fr 33.29 \ft found…: or, subdued\f*
